{"questionId":"9084586","questionHtml":"<p>Ball 1 collides with an initially stationary ball 2 of the same mass. After the collision, the balls move with speeds <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. Their velocities make angles <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;with the original direction of motion of ball 1.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e1b7733e1b4027e571c97f93970c7505d59b538e.png\"></p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084586","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.HL.TZ0.2","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment